Class AddressCorrection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.guidewire.pl.persistence.code.BeanBase
      • entity.AddressCorrection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.guidewire.commons.entity.Keyable, com.guidewire.commons.entity.Sourceable, com.guidewire.pl.persistence.core.BeanMethods, KeyableBean, Versionable, Bean, BundleProvider, java.lang.Comparable<Bean>

    @Generated(value="com.guidewire.pl.metadata.codegen.Codegen",
           comments="AddressCorrection.eti;AddressCorrection.eix;AddressCorrection.etx")
public class AddressCorrection
extends com.guidewire.pl.persistence.code.BeanBase
implements Versionable
    AddressCorrection Encapsulates a copy of those fields within a persistent Address which represent a physical address, at the point in time it was Geocoded, and any corrected fields received upon Geocoding that Address.

    AddressCorrection entities will not be created for temporary Address, if no corrections are received, or if Geocoding fails for that Address. If an Address is edited more than once, and the Geocoding is updated, more than one AddressCorrection may exist for a given address.

    Note that the corrected address may not capture all information from the original; in particular, MapPoint will discard apartment/suite/floor/mailstop numbers. Similarly, "duplicate" corrections may be produced.
